definition.value: A sulfated glycosaminoglycan, a linear polymer that consists of the repeating disaccharide  [3)-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-GlcNAc-(1->] and containing sulfo groups located at random positions.
A 6-O-acyl-D-glucose where the acyl group is 3-hydroxy-2-tetradecyldotriacontanoyl.
Any  amino sugar that is a monosaccharide in which one alcoholic hydroxy group is replaced by an amino group.

A polycyclic ether comprising a central oxepine ring flanked by two fused tetrahydropyran rings together with a spiro-fused tetrahydrofuran ring. Corresponds to the JKLM ring fragment and epitope of ciguatoxin.
An amino trisaccharide comprising an N-acetyl beta-D-galactosaminyl residue flanked by two D-galactopyranose residues (one at the reducing end).
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by removing two protons from the phosphate group of arbutin 6-phosphate.
An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetylgalactosamine having an alpha-D-galactosyl residue at the 4-position
An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetylgalactosamine having an alpha-D-galactosyl residue at the 3-position
An acyl-CoA oxoanion obtained from (R)-carnitinyl-CoA betaine in which three protons have been removed from the phosphate groups.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (E)-4-(trimethylammonio)but-2-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of any alcohol with sinapic acid.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of two D-galactose residues and an N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residue (at the reducing end) in a linear sequence.
A hydrochloride salt obtained from equimola amounts of moricizine and hydrogen chloride.
A xylan composed of a beta-(1->4)-linked D-xylose backbone substituted with glucuronic acid residues.
A D-mannoside of D-glyceric acid.
A derivative of the amino acid cysteine formed by the covalent addition of a prenyl residue.
A HETE having a 5-hydroxy group and (6E)-, (8Z)-, (11Z)- and (14Z)-double bonds.
An alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc in which the anomeric centre at the reducing end has alpha-configuration.
An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosminyl resiude attached at the 4-position.
A linear trisaccharide comprising D-glucose (at the reducing end) having an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety at the 4-position.
A linear trisaccharide comprising D-glucose (at the reducing end) having an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety at the 4-position.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of two D-galactose residues and an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue (at the reducing end) in a linear sequence.
Any of a group of water-soluble phenolic derivatives containing a flavan skeleton, which possess antibiotic activity and are produced by plant tissues in response to infection.

A class of diterpene formed in plants in response to fungal infection, physical damage, chemical injury, or a pathogenic process; they are sometimes referred to as plant antibiotics. Diterpenes are unsaturated hydrocarbons containing 20 carbon atoms and 4 branched methyl groups and are made up of isoprenoid units.
A cyanohydrin in which the substituents on the alpha carbon are ethyl and methyl.
A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of 9(S)-HPODE.
A long-chain, divinyl ether fatty acid composed of 8-nonenoic acid having the E- hydrogen at position 9 substituted by a (1E,3Z)-nona-1,3,-dien-1-yloxy group.
An oxo fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of colneleic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A synthetic seven-membered oligopeptide comprising N-acetyl-3-cyclohexyl-L-alanyl, L-arginyl, L-alanyl, L-methionyl, L-alanyl, L-seryl and L-leucinamide residues coupled in sequence.
A long-chain, divinyl ether fatty acid composed of 8-nonenoic acid in which the E-hydrogen at position 9 is substituted by a (1E,3Z,6Z)-nona-1,3,6-trien-1-yloxy group.
A oxa fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of colnelenic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A (10E,12Z,15Z)-9-hydroperoxyoctadeca-10,12,15-trienoic acid which has S-configuration at the chiral centre.
A (10E,12Z,15Z)-9-hydroperoxyoctadeca-10,12,15-trienoate in which the chiral centre has S configuration.

A polyanionic heteropolysaccharide containing a repeat unit with D-glucose, L-fucose, D-galactose, and D-glucuronic acid sugars that are non-stoichiometrically decorated with O-acetyl and pyruvate side-chains
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Tic, Haic, Ser and MeLeu-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Tic and Met-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Cpg, Tic and Met-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Disc and Met-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A sesquiterpenoid consisting of a tricyclic carbon skeleton functionalised by a tertiary hydroxy group.
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Cpg, Disc and Met-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic pentapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Tic, Met and betaPhPro-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A phospholipid that contains one or more amino groups.
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Tic, Met, betaPhPro and [S(oxaz)L]-NMe2 residues coupled in sequence.
A complex lipophilic polymer macromolecule, containing a fatty acid-derived domain (aliphatic suberin) and a (poly)hydroxycinnamate domain (aromatic suberin).
A non-proteinogenic amino acid modified by the addition of a cyano group.
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Gpg, Tic, Met, betaPhPro and [S(oxaz)L]-NMe2 residues coupled in sequence.
